      <h2>Construction &amp; Renovation in Wailuku</h2>
      <p>Wailuku is the heart of Maui — the county seat, the administrative center, and one of the island's oldest continuously inhabited communities. Where Kahului serves as Maui's commercial and logistics hub, Wailuku is the civic center: Maui County government offices, the courts, and the dense mix of businesses, residences, and historic buildings that line Market Street, Main Street, and the neighborhoods climbing toward Iao Valley.</p>

      <p>The built environment in Wailuku reflects that history. Many of the homes and commercial buildings in historic Wailuku Town date from the early to mid-20th century — plantation-era structures with specific renovation challenges and, in some cases, historic preservation considerations. Alongside these older buildings, Wailuku's residential neighborhoods extend up into the hills toward Iao Valley and spread across Central Maui, encompassing a wide range of home types from small plantation cottages to larger modern residences.</p>

      <p>Great General LLC works throughout this landscape. We renovate plantation-era homes with awareness of their specific construction methods and materials, handle modern residential renovations in Wailuku's newer neighborhoods, and provide commercial tenant improvement services for businesses in downtown Wailuku and the surrounding commercial areas.</p>

      <h2>Historic Wailuku Town</h2>
      <p>Downtown Wailuku — centered on Market Street, Main Street, and the surrounding blocks — is one of Maui's most architecturally significant areas. The historic commercial buildings that line these streets are home to a mix of local businesses, restaurants, government offices, and community organizations. Renovation work in this area often involves buildings with historic character that requires careful handling.</p>

      <p>We approach renovation work in historic Wailuku with respect for the character of the buildings and awareness of the applicable regulatory environment. Some properties in this area are on the State or National Historic Register, triggering review requirements beyond standard Maui County permitting. We factor these considerations into project planning from the start and won't promise work that isn't properly permitted and reviewed.</p>

      <h2>Wailuku Residential Renovation</h2>
      <p>Wailuku's residential neighborhoods span a wide range of housing types and vintages. The areas immediately surrounding downtown include many of Maui's oldest homes — small plantation cottages and Craftsman-influenced bungalows from the early 20th century. These homes have distinctive character and often genuine historic value, but they also come with specific renovation challenges: older framing systems, materials that predate modern building codes, lead paint and asbestos in pre-1980 construction, and floor plans that reflect a different era of living patterns.</p>

      <p>We work on homes like these regularly. Renovation of older Wailuku properties requires demolition awareness (what's behind the wall matters), framing knowledge to understand what's structural, and the skill to integrate modern finishes and systems into older structures without destroying their character. It's specialized work, and we do it well.</p>

      <p>The newer residential areas of Wailuku — the subdivisions extending toward Happy Valley, Waiehu, and the communities along Waiehu Beach Road and Kahekili Highway — present a different profile. These homes are more conventional in construction and more straightforward in renovation scope: kitchen remodels, bathroom renovations, flooring replacement, and whole-home updates are common project types. We serve homeowners throughout these neighborhoods.</p>

      <h2>Iao Valley Area Properties</h2>
      <p>The neighborhoods climbing up toward Iao Valley — including the homes along Iao Valley Road and the residential streets that branch off it — are among Wailuku's most desirable, offering mountain views, cooler temperatures, and a sense of remove from the busier parts of Central Maui. Properties here tend to be on larger lots with more complex terrain. We handle renovation and construction projects in this area including structural work, exterior improvements, and custom metalwork for gates and fencing on hillside properties.</p>

      <h2>Commercial Tenant Improvements in Wailuku</h2>
      <p>Wailuku's commercial district, and the office and retail buildings that surround the county government campus, host a steady stream of tenant improvement projects as businesses move in, expand, or reconfigure their spaces. We provide commercial general contracting and tenant improvement services for Wailuku businesses — interior buildouts, office reconfigurations, retail renovations, and small commercial construction — with permit management and county coordination included.</p>

      <h2>Central Maui Reach</h2>
      <p>From Wailuku, we serve the full Central Maui region including the adjacent communities of Waiehu, Waihe'e, Happy Valley, and the neighborhoods connecting Wailuku to Kahului along the highway corridor. We also serve the residential areas above Wailuku toward the base of the West Maui Mountains. There's no corner of Central Maui that's out of our service area.</p>

      <h2>Services Available in Wailuku</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>General contracting and full project management for residential and commercial projects</li>
        <li>Kitchen and bathroom remodels in Wailuku homes, including older plantation-era properties</li>
        <li>Interior framing, drywall, and buildout work throughout the residential and commercial market</li>
        <li>Selective and full demolition, including older construction materials</li>
        <li>Custom carpentry and millwork for both historic renovations and modern finishes</li>
        <li>Metal fabrication — custom gates, railings, and fencing for Wailuku residential and commercial properties</li>
        <li>Maui County permit management, including coordination with the county offices that are literally down the street</li>
        <li>Commercial tenant improvements for downtown Wailuku and surrounding commercial areas</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Free On-Site Estimates in Wailuku</h2>
      <p>We visit properties throughout Wailuku and Central Maui for free on-site estimates. Whether you're planning a kitchen renovation in a historic Wailuku bungalow, a commercial tenant improvement in a Market Street building, or a full residential remodel in one of Wailuku's hillside neighborhoods, we'll come to you and give you a clear, written estimate. Call (808) 795-4044 or request an estimate online.</p>
